{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"Chris Anderson: Perhaps we could start\nby just telling us about your country."},{"time":4440,"text":"It's three dots there on the globe.\nThose dots are pretty huge."},{"time":8320,"text":"I think each one\nis about the size of California."},{"time":11000,"text":"Tell us about Kiribati."}]},{"cues":[{"time":12880,"text":"Anote Tong: Well, let me first begin\nby saying how deeply grateful I am"},{"time":17400,"text":"for this opportunity to share my story\nwith people who do care."},{"time":21560,"text":"I think I've been sharing my story with\na lot of people who don't care too much."},{"time":27160,"text":"But Kiribati is comprised\nof three groups of islands:"},{"time":31040,"text":"the Gilbert Group on the west,"},{"time":33880,"text":"we have the Phoenix Islands in the middle,"},{"time":37240,"text":"and the Line Islands in the east."},{"time":41680,"text":"And quite frankly, Kiribati\nis perhaps the only country"},{"time":44800,"text":"that is actually\nin the four corners of the world,"},{"time":47166,"text":"because we are in the Northern Hemisphere,\nin the Southern Hemisphere,"},{"time":50490,"text":"and also in the east and the west\nof the International Date Line."},{"time":53570,"text":"These islands are entirely\nmade up of coral atolls,"},{"time":59920,"text":"and on average about\ntwo meters above sea level."},{"time":64879,"text":"And so this is what we have."},{"time":68360,"text":"Usually not more\nthan two kilometers in width."},{"time":73200,"text":"And so, on many occasions,\nI've been asked by people,"},{"time":76160,"text":"\"You know, you're suffering,\nwhy don't you move back?\""},{"time":78720,"text":"They don't understand."},{"time":79960,"text":"They have no concept\nof what it is that's involved."},{"time":83680,"text":"With the rising sea, they say,\n\"Well, you can move back.\""},{"time":87280,"text":"And so this is what I tell them."},{"time":88880,"text":"If we move back, we will fall off\non the other side of the ocean. OK?"},{"time":93240,"text":"But these are the kinds of issues\nthat people don't understand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98040,"text":"CA: So certainly this is\njust a picture of fragility there."},{"time":102280,"text":"When was it that you yourself realized"},{"time":104840,"text":"that there might be\nimpending peril for your country?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":108480,"text":"AT: Well, the story of climate change\nhas been one that has been going on"},{"time":111960,"text":"for quite a number of decades."},{"time":113440,"text":"And when I came into office in 2003,"},{"time":118200,"text":"I began talking about climate change\nat the United Nations General Assembly,"},{"time":122480,"text":"but not with so much passion,"},{"time":125240,"text":"because then there was still\nthis controversy among the scientists"},{"time":128880,"text":"whether it was human-induced,\nwhether it was real or it wasn't."},{"time":134160,"text":"But I think that that debate\nwas fairly much concluded in 2007"},{"time":140320,"text":"with the Fourth Assessment\nReport of the IPCC,"},{"time":145920,"text":"which made a categorical statement\nthat it is real, it's human-induced,"},{"time":152800,"text":"and it's predicting\nsome very serious scenarios"},{"time":156760,"text":"for countries like mine."},{"time":159320,"text":"And so that's when I got very serious."},{"time":162600,"text":"In the past, I talked about it."},{"time":166600,"text":"We were worried."},{"time":167840,"text":"But when the scenarios,\nthe predictions came in 2007,"},{"time":171600,"text":"it became a real issue for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173960,"text":"CA: Now, those predictions are,\nI think, that by 2100,"},{"time":179600,"text":"sea levels are forecast to rise\nperhaps three feet."},{"time":182400,"text":"There's scenarios where\nit's higher than that, for sure,"},{"time":185044,"text":"but what would you say\nto a skeptic who said,"},{"time":187204,"text":"\"What's three feet?"},{"time":188400,"text":"You're on average\nsix feet above sea level."},{"time":190600,"text":"What's the problem?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":192200,"text":"AT: Well, I think\nit's got to be understood"},{"time":194280,"text":"that a marginal rise in sea level"},{"time":196360,"text":"would mean a loss of a lot of land,"},{"time":198960,"text":"because much of the land is low."},{"time":202240,"text":"And quite apart from that,\nwe are getting the swells at the moment."},{"time":207360,"text":"So it's not about getting two feet."},{"time":209560,"text":"I think what many people do not understand"},{"time":212600,"text":"is they think climate change is something\nthat is happening in the future."},{"time":218800,"text":"Well, we're at the very\nbottom end of the spectrum."},{"time":221640,"text":"It's already with us."},{"time":222920,"text":"We have communities\nwho already have been dislocated."},{"time":226760,"text":"They have had to move,\nand every parliament session,"},{"time":230720,"text":"I'm getting complaints\nfrom different communities"},{"time":233080,"text":"asking for assistance to build seawalls,"},{"time":236160,"text":"to see what we can do\nabout the freshwater lens"},{"time":238720,"text":"because it's being destroyed,"},{"time":240560,"text":"and so in my trips\nto the different islands,"},{"time":243320,"text":"I'm seeing evidence of communities"},{"time":246040,"text":"which are now having to cope\nwith the loss of food crops,"},{"time":249680,"text":"the contamination of the water lenses,"},{"time":253280,"text":"and I see these communities\nperhaps leaving, having to relocate,"},{"time":257640,"text":"within five to 10 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260000,"text":"CA: And then, I think the country\nsuffered its first cyclone,"},{"time":263960,"text":"and this is connected, yes?\nWhat happened here?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":267520,"text":"AT: Well, we're on the equator,"},{"time":270240,"text":"and I'm sure many of you understand\nthat when you're on the equator,"},{"time":274680,"text":"it's supposed to be in the doldrums.\nWe're not supposed to get the cyclones."},{"time":278280,"text":"We create them, and then we send them\neither north or south."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281114,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":282520,"text":"But they aren't supposed to come back."},{"time":284400,"text":"But for the first time,\nat the beginning of this year,"},{"time":286948,"text":"the Cyclone Pam,\nwhich destroyed Vanuatu,"},{"time":290640,"text":"and in the process,\nthe very edges of it actually touched"},{"time":294120,"text":"our two southernmost islands,"},{"time":296520,"text":"and all of Tuvalu was underwater\nwhen Hurricane Pam struck."},{"time":301920,"text":"But for our two southernmost islands,"},{"time":305640,"text":"we had waves come over half the island,"},{"time":309000,"text":"and so this has never happened before."},{"time":311480,"text":"It's a new experience."},{"time":313080,"text":"And I've just come back\nfrom my own constituency,"},{"time":318440,"text":"and I've seen these beautiful trees\nwhich had been there for decades,"},{"time":321800,"text":"they've been totally destroyed."},{"time":323800,"text":"So this is what's happening,"},{"time":325520,"text":"but when we talk\nabout the rising sea level,"},{"time":329400,"text":"we think it's something\nthat happens gradually."},{"time":332520,"text":"It comes with the winds,\nit comes with the swells,"},{"time":335600,"text":"and so they can be magnified,"},{"time":337560,"text":"but what we are beginning to witness\nis the change in the weather pattern,"},{"time":343760,"text":"which is perhaps the more urgent challenge"},{"time":346520,"text":"that we will face sooner\nthan perhaps the rising sea level."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351080,"text":"CA: So the country\nis already seeing effects now."},{"time":354360,"text":"As you look forward,"},{"time":356560,"text":"what are your options\nas a country, as a nation?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":360520,"text":"AT: Well, I've been telling\nthis story every year."},{"time":363200,"text":"I think I visit a number of --"},{"time":364653,"text":"I've been traveling the world\nto try and get people to understand."},{"time":369640,"text":"We have a plan, we think we have a plan."},{"time":372120,"text":"And on one occasion,\nI think I spoke in Geneva"},{"time":375560,"text":"and there was a gentleman\nwho was interviewing me"},{"time":379760,"text":"on something like this,"},{"time":381520,"text":"and I said, \"We are looking\nat floating islands,\""},{"time":383880,"text":"and he thought it was funny,\nbut somebody said,"},{"time":386120,"text":"\"No, this is not funny.\nThese people are looking for solutions.\""},{"time":390080,"text":"And so I have been looking\nat floating islands."},{"time":393640,"text":"The Japanese are interested\nin building floating islands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397400,"text":"But, as a country,\nwe have made a commitment"},{"time":400360,"text":"that no matter what happens,\nwe will try as much as possible"},{"time":404080,"text":"to stay and continue to exist as a nation."},{"time":408280,"text":"What that will take,"},{"time":409840,"text":"it's going to be\nsomething quite significant,"},{"time":413280,"text":"very, very substantial."},{"time":415320,"text":"Either we live on floating islands,"},{"time":417120,"text":"or we have to build up the islands\nto continue to stay out of the water"},{"time":421120,"text":"as the sea level rises\nand as the storms get more severe."},{"time":425880,"text":"But even that, it's going to be\nvery, very difficult"},{"time":428333,"text":"to get the kind of resourcing\nthat we would need."}]},{"cues":[{"time":431200,"text":"CA: And then the only recourse\nis some form of forced migration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435080,"text":"AT: Well, we are also looking at that"},{"time":437320,"text":"because in the event\nthat nothing comes forward"},{"time":440240,"text":"from the international community,"},{"time":442080,"text":"we are preparing,"},{"time":443360,"text":"we don't want to be caught\nlike what's happening in Europe."},{"time":446600,"text":"OK? We don't want to mass migrate\nat some point in time."},{"time":449320,"text":"We want to be able\nto give the people the choice today,"},{"time":452760,"text":"those who choose\nand want to do that, to migrate."},{"time":456440,"text":"We don't want something to happen\nthat they are forced to migrate"},{"time":461520,"text":"without having been prepared to do so."},{"time":463840,"text":"Of course, our culture is very different,\nour society is very different,"},{"time":467360,"text":"and once we migrate\ninto a different environment,"},{"time":469720,"text":"a different culture,"},{"time":470960,"text":"there's a whole lot\nof adjustments that are required."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473920,"text":"CA: Well, there's forced migration\nin your country's past,"},{"time":477200,"text":"and I think just this week,"},{"time":478880,"text":"just yesterday\nor the day before yesterday,"},{"time":482160,"text":"you visited these people."},{"time":484360,"text":"What happened here? What's the story here?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":486560,"text":"AT: Yes, and I'm sorry,\nI think somebody was asking"},{"time":489000,"text":"why we were sneaking off\nto visit that place."},{"time":492000,"text":"I had a very good reason, because we have\na community of Kiribati people"},{"time":496000,"text":"living in that part\nof the Solomon Islands,"},{"time":500120,"text":"but these were people who were relocated\nfrom the Phoenix Islands, in fact,"},{"time":504000,"text":"in the 1960s."},{"time":505480,"text":"There was serious drought, and the people\ncould not continue to live on the island,"},{"time":510040,"text":"and so they were moved\nto live here in the Solomon Islands."},{"time":513440,"text":"And so yesterday it was very interesting\nto meet with these people."},{"time":516640,"text":"They didn't know who I was.\nThey hadn't heard of me."},{"time":519120,"text":"Some of them later recognized me,"},{"time":521720,"text":"but I think they were very happy."},{"time":525320,"text":"Later they really wanted to have\nthe opportunity to welcome me formally."},{"time":529760,"text":"But I think what I saw yesterday\nwas very interesting"},{"time":533040,"text":"because here I see our people."},{"time":534880,"text":"I spoke in our language, and of course\nthey spoke back, they replied,"},{"time":540720,"text":"but their accent, they are beginning\nnot to be able to speak Kiribati properly."},{"time":545440,"text":"I saw them, there was\nthis lady with red teeth."},{"time":547960,"text":"She was chewing betel nuts,"},{"time":550200,"text":"and it's not something we do in Kiribati."},{"time":552480,"text":"We don't chew betel nuts."},{"time":555120,"text":"I met also a family who have married\nthe local people here,"},{"time":561000,"text":"and so this is what is happening."},{"time":565120,"text":"As you go into another community,\nthere are bound to be changes."},{"time":568720,"text":"There is bound to be\na certain loss of identity,"},{"time":573200,"text":"and this is what we will be\nlooking for in the future"},{"time":576680,"text":"if and when we do migrate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578960,"text":"CA: It must have been\njust an extraordinarily emotional day"},{"time":582160,"text":"because of these questions about identity,"},{"time":585000,"text":"the joy of seeing you and perhaps\nan emphasized sense of what they had lost."},{"time":590240,"text":"And it's very inspiring to hear you say\nyou're going to fight to the end"},{"time":593645,"text":"to try to preserve\nthe nation in a location."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598080,"text":"AT: This is our wish."},{"time":599400,"text":"Nobody wants ever to leave their home,"},{"time":602480,"text":"and so it's been\na very difficult decision for me."},{"time":605560,"text":"As a leader, you don't make plans\nto leave your island, your home,"},{"time":610960,"text":"and so I've been asked\non a number of occasions,"},{"time":613240,"text":"\"So how do you feel?\""},{"time":614480,"text":"And it doesn't feel good at all."},{"time":617640,"text":"It's an emotional thing,\nand I've tried to live with it,"},{"time":621240,"text":"and I know that on occasions, I'm accused\nof not trying to solve the problem"},{"time":626200,"text":"because I can't solve the problem."},{"time":628200,"text":"It's something that's got\nto be done collectively."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631040,"text":"Climate change is a global phenomenon,\nand as I've often argued,"},{"time":636840,"text":"unfortunately, the countries,\nwhen we come to the United Nations --"},{"time":641360,"text":"I was in a meeting with\nthe Pacific Island Forum countries"},{"time":646280,"text":"where Australia and New Zealand\nare also members,"},{"time":648800,"text":"and we had an argument."},{"time":650560,"text":"There was a bit of a story in the news"},{"time":653280,"text":"because they were arguing\nthat to cut emissions,"},{"time":657600,"text":"it would be something\nthat they're unable to do"},{"time":659880,"text":"because it would affect the industries."},{"time":663120,"text":"And so here I was saying,"},{"time":664600,"text":"OK, I hear you,"},{"time":666840,"text":"I understand what you're saying,"},{"time":668520,"text":"but try also to understand what I'm saying"},{"time":670800,"text":"because if you do not cut your emissions,"},{"time":673440,"text":"then our survival is on the line."},{"time":675840,"text":"And so it's a matter for you\nto weigh this, these moral issues."},{"time":680200,"text":"It's about industry as opposed to\nthe survival of a people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":684240,"text":"CA: You know, I ask you yesterday\nwhat made you angry,"},{"time":686920,"text":"and you said, \"I don't get angry.\"\nBut then you paused."},{"time":690440,"text":"I think this made you angry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692080,"text":"AT: I'd refer you to my earlier\nstatement at the United Nations."},{"time":697000,"text":"I was very angry, very frustrated\nand then depressed."},{"time":701960,"text":"There was a sense of futility"},{"time":703960,"text":"that we are fighting a fight\nthat we have no hope of winning."},{"time":709440,"text":"I had to change my approach."},{"time":711640,"text":"I had to become more reasonable"},{"time":713760,"text":"because I thought people would listen\nto somebody who was rational,"},{"time":716927,"text":"but I remain radically rational,\nwhatever that is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":721160,"text":"CA: Now, a core part\nof your nation's identity is fishing."},{"time":724920,"text":"I think you said pretty much everyone\nis involved in fishing in some way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728440,"text":"AT: Well, we eat fish\nevery day, every day,"},{"time":731240,"text":"and I think there is no doubt\nthat our rate of consumption of fish"},{"time":735800,"text":"is perhaps the highest in the world."},{"time":737960,"text":"We don't have a lot of livestock,"},{"time":740440,"text":"so it's fish that we depend on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":743240,"text":"CA: So you're dependent on fish,\nboth at the local level"},{"time":746400,"text":"and for the revenues\nthat the country receives"},{"time":749120,"text":"from the global fishing business for tuna,"},{"time":751720,"text":"and yet despite that, a few years ago\nyou took a very radical step."},{"time":756640,"text":"Can you tell us about that?"},{"time":758040,"text":"I think something happened\nright here in the Phoenix Islands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":761400,"text":"AT: Let me give some of the background\nof what fish means for us."},{"time":766720,"text":"We have one of the largest\ntuna fisheries remaining in the world."},{"time":770680,"text":"In the Pacific, I think we own\nsomething like 60 percent"},{"time":773560,"text":"of the remaining tuna fisheries,"},{"time":775480,"text":"and it remains relatively healthy\nfor some species, but not all."},{"time":779760,"text":"And Kiribati is one of the three\nmajor resource owners,"},{"time":785920,"text":"tuna resource owners."},{"time":787640,"text":"And at the moment, we have been getting"},{"time":791240,"text":"something like 80 to 90\npercent of our revenue"},{"time":794160,"text":"from access fees, license fees."}]},{"cues":[{"time":796640,"text":"CA: Of your national revenue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":798520,"text":"AT: National revenue,"},{"time":800360,"text":"which drives everything that we do"},{"time":803200,"text":"in governments, hospitals,\nschools and what have you."},{"time":807240,"text":"But we decided to close this,\nand it was a very difficult decision."},{"time":812480,"text":"I can assure you, politically,\nlocally, it was not easy,"},{"time":818040,"text":"but I was convinced that we had to do this"},{"time":822000,"text":"in order to ensure\nthat the fishery remains sustainable."},{"time":826600,"text":"There had been some indications\nthat some of the species,"},{"time":829400,"text":"in particular the bigeye,\nwas under serious threat."},{"time":833560,"text":"The yellowfin was also heavily fished."},{"time":836960,"text":"Skipjack remains healthy."},{"time":838720,"text":"And so we had to do something like that,\nand so that was the reason I did that."},{"time":843520,"text":"Another reason why I did that"},{"time":847440,"text":"was because I had been asking\nthe international community"},{"time":852160,"text":"that in order to deal with climate change,\nin order to fight climate change,"},{"time":856720,"text":"there has got to be sacrifice,\nthere has got to be commitment."},{"time":860640,"text":"So in asking the international community\nto make a sacrifice,"},{"time":865960,"text":"I thought we ourselves\nneed to make that sacrifice."},{"time":868800,"text":"And so we made the sacrifice."},{"time":870640,"text":"And forgoing commercial fishing"},{"time":875608,"text":"in the Phoenix Islands protected area"},{"time":878240,"text":"would mean a loss of revenue."},{"time":880120,"text":"We are still trying to assess\nwhat that loss would be"},{"time":882621,"text":"because we actually closed it off\nat the beginning of this year,"},{"time":887880,"text":"and so we will see by the end of this year"},{"time":890240,"text":"what it means in terms\nof the lost revenue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":893760,"text":"CA: So there's so many things\nplaying into this."},{"time":896040,"text":"On the one hand,\nit may prompt healthier fisheries."},{"time":903040,"text":"I mean, how much are you able\nto move the price up"},{"time":905440,"text":"that you charge for the remaining areas?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":907960,"text":"AT: The negotiations\nhave been very difficult,"},{"time":912600,"text":"but we have managed\nto raise the cost of a vessel day."},{"time":916480,"text":"For any vessel\nto come in to fish for a day,"},{"time":919120,"text":"we have raised the fee from --\nit was $6,000 and $8,000,"},{"time":922760,"text":"now to $10,000, $12,000 per vessel day."},{"time":927360,"text":"And so there's been\nthat significant increase."},{"time":930600,"text":"But at the same time,\nwhat's important to note is,"},{"time":935200,"text":"whereas in the past these fishing boats"},{"time":939560,"text":"might be fishing in a day\nand maybe catch 10 tons,"},{"time":943520,"text":"now they're catching maybe 100 tons\nbecause they've become so efficient."},{"time":947440,"text":"And so we've got to respond likewise."},{"time":949800,"text":"We've got to be very, very careful\nbecause the technology has so improved."},{"time":954000,"text":"There was a time when the Brazilian fleet\nmoved from the Atlantic to the Pacific."},{"time":959440,"text":"They couldn't."},{"time":960680,"text":"They started experimenting\nif they could, per se."},{"time":963920,"text":"But now they've got ways of doing it,\nand they've become so efficient."}]},{"cues":[{"time":969000,"text":"CA: Can you give us a sense\nof what it's like in those negotiations?"},{"time":972223,"text":"Because you're up against companies"},{"time":973944,"text":"that have hundreds of millions\nof dollars at stake, essentially."},{"time":977560,"text":"How do you hold the line?"},{"time":980920,"text":"Is there any advice you can give"},{"time":983000,"text":"to other leaders who are dealing\nwith the same companies"},{"time":986080,"text":"about how to get\nthe most for your country,"},{"time":990400,"text":"get the most for the fish?"},{"time":994440,"text":"What advice would you give?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":996000,"text":"AT: Well, I think we focus\ntoo often on licensing"},{"time":1002280,"text":"in order to get the rate of return,"},{"time":1003971,"text":"because what we are getting\nfrom license fees"},{"time":1006800,"text":"is about 10 percent\nof the landed value of the catch"},{"time":1009440,"text":"on the side of the wharf,\nnot in the retail shops."},{"time":1012600,"text":"And we only get about 10 percent."},{"time":1016600,"text":"What we have been trying\nto do over the years"},{"time":1019240,"text":"is actually to increase\nour participation in the industry,"},{"time":1023120,"text":"in the harvesting, in the processing,"},{"time":1025760,"text":"and eventually, hopefully, the marketing."},{"time":1027642,"text":"They're not easy to penetrate,"},{"time":1031359,"text":"but we are working towards that,"},{"time":1033680,"text":"and yes, the answer would be to enhance."},{"time":1036319,"text":"In order to increase our rate of return,\nwe have to become more involved."},{"time":1040560,"text":"And so we've started doing that,"},{"time":1043760,"text":"and we have to restructure the industry."},{"time":1048040,"text":"We've got to tell these people\nthat the world has changed."},{"time":1051440,"text":"Now we want to produce the fish ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1053880,"text":"CA: And meanwhile,\nfor your local fishermen,"},{"time":1056000,"text":"they are still able to fish,"},{"time":1059120,"text":"but what is business like for them?"},{"time":1061600,"text":"Is it getting harder?\nAre the waters depleted?"},{"time":1063960,"text":"Or is that being run\non a sustainable basis?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1067440,"text":"AT: For the artisanal fishery,"},{"time":1068920,"text":"we do not participate\nin the commercial fishing activity"},{"time":1072200,"text":"except only to supply the domestic market."},{"time":1075240,"text":"The tuna fishery is really\nentirely for the foreign market,"},{"time":1078560,"text":"mostly here in the US, Europe, Japan."},{"time":1084800,"text":"So I am a fisherman, very much,"},{"time":1089360,"text":"and I used to be able to catch yellowfin."},{"time":1092560,"text":"Now it's very, very rare\nto be able to catch yellowfin"},{"time":1095360,"text":"because they are being lifted\nout of the water by the hundreds of tons"},{"time":1098760,"text":"by these purse seiners."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1102360,"text":"CA: So here's a couple\nof beautiful girls from your country."},{"time":1107320,"text":"I mean, as you think about their future,"},{"time":1110560,"text":"what message would you have for them"},{"time":1113240,"text":"and what message\nwould you have for the world?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1116280,"text":"AT: Well, I've been telling the world\nthat we really have to do something"},{"time":1119733,"text":"about what is happening to the climate"},{"time":1121600,"text":"because for us, it's about\nthe future of these children."},{"time":1124400,"text":"I have 12 grandchildren, at least."},{"time":1126360,"text":"I think I have 12, my wife knows."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1128400,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1130640,"text":"And I think I have eight children."},{"time":1133680,"text":"It's about their future."},{"time":1134960,"text":"Every day I see my grandchildren,\nabout the same age as these young girls,"},{"time":1138720,"text":"and I do wonder,"},{"time":1141160,"text":"and I get angry sometimes, yes I do."},{"time":1143400,"text":"I wonder what is to become of them."},{"time":1145480,"text":"And so it's about them"},{"time":1148640,"text":"that we should be telling everybody,"},{"time":1150920,"text":"that it's not about\ntheir own national interest,"},{"time":1153200,"text":"because climate change,\nregrettably, unfortunately,"},{"time":1156880,"text":"is viewed by many countries\nas a national problem. It's not."},{"time":1161000,"text":"And this is the argument\nwe got into recently with our partners,"},{"time":1164024,"text":"the Australians and New Zealanders,"},{"time":1165744,"text":"because they said,\n\"We can't cut any more.\""},{"time":1169080,"text":"This is what one of the leaders,\nthe Australian leader, said,"},{"time":1172720,"text":"that we've done our part,\nwe are cutting back."},{"time":1177000,"text":"I said, What about the rest?\nWhy don't you keep it?"},{"time":1180680,"text":"If you could keep\nthe rest of your emissions"},{"time":1183400,"text":"within your boundaries,\nwithin your borders,"},{"time":1185720,"text":"we'd have no question."},{"time":1187520,"text":"You can go ahead as much as you like."},{"time":1189360,"text":"But unfortunately,\nyou're sending it our way,"},{"time":1191520,"text":"and it's affecting\nthe future of our children."},{"time":1193735,"text":"And so surely I think that is the heart\nof the problem of climate change today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1198800,"text":"We will be meeting in Paris\nat the end of this year,"},{"time":1201880,"text":"but until we can think of this\nas a global phenomenon,"},{"time":1205840,"text":"because we create it,\nindividually, as nations,"},{"time":1209120,"text":"but it affects everybody else,"},{"time":1211080,"text":"and yet, we refuse\nto do anything about it,"},{"time":1214720,"text":"and we deal with it as a national problem,"},{"time":1217200,"text":"which it is not -- it is a global issue,"},{"time":1219320,"text":"and it's got to be\ndealt with collectively."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1223120,"text":"CA: People are incredibly bad\nat responding to graphs and numbers,"},{"time":1227480,"text":"and we shut our minds to it."},{"time":1231280,"text":"Somehow, to people, we're slightly better\nat responding to that sometimes."},{"time":1237560,"text":"And it seems like it's\nvery possible that your nation,"},{"time":1240520,"text":"despite, actually because of\nthe intense problems you face,"},{"time":1245000,"text":"you may yet be the warning light\nto the world that shines most visibly,"},{"time":1249920,"text":"most powerfully."},{"time":1251920,"text":"I just want to thank you, \nI'm sure, on behalf of all of us,"},{"time":1254762,"text":"for your extraordinary leadership\nand for being here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1257280,"text":"Mr. President, thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1258873,"text":"AT: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1259666,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}